WEBVTT

00:01.169 --> 00:03.003
CLAIRE: Previously,
on The Good Doctor...

00:03.037 --> 00:05.906
FEMALE VOICE: Message
received from Mom.
(BEEP)

00:05.939 --> 00:07.775
BREEZE: Hey, baby.
I got your text.

00:07.808 --> 00:10.311
We're gonna celebrate.
I'll see you soon.

00:10.344 --> 00:12.480
I'm so proud of you, baby!

00:12.513 --> 00:13.847
**

00:14.648 --> 00:17.285
Here are flowers
and chocolates.

00:17.318 --> 00:19.620
Are you asking me out?
Yes.

00:19.653 --> 00:20.821
I would love to.

00:20.854 --> 00:22.022
(GASPS)

00:23.857 --> 00:26.860
**

00:44.645 --> 00:47.248
Will we be doing this
during all the
commercials?

00:48.716 --> 00:50.351
It's possible.

00:51.485 --> 00:52.686
Hmm.

01:04.532 --> 01:06.066
(REMOTE CLICKS)

01:06.100 --> 01:08.136
DR. ANDREWS:
Patient came in through
the celebrity track.

01:08.169 --> 01:10.171
He was admitted
through an entrance
by the loading dock.

01:10.204 --> 01:12.039
You're not to mention
his name even
to your colleagues.

01:12.072 --> 01:13.174
What is his name?

01:13.207 --> 01:14.375
Mitchell Stewart.

01:14.408 --> 01:17.211
The conspiracy theorist?
That's a celebrity now?

01:17.245 --> 01:19.513
A guy who thinks
9/11 was an inside job?

01:19.547 --> 01:20.681
He's an ass.

01:20.714 --> 01:22.550
He's an ass
who needs liver surgery.

01:24.552 --> 01:26.354
Whoa, whoa.
Hold it right there.

01:26.387 --> 01:28.389
Uhp! It's okay, Dex.
They're on the list.

01:29.290 --> 01:32.860
Drs. Murphy,
Park, Andrews.

01:32.893 --> 01:34.061
Mitchell Stewart.

01:34.094 --> 01:35.763
I don't blindly turn over
my well-being,

01:35.796 --> 01:37.365
or anything else,
to those in authority,

01:37.398 --> 01:39.367
so I ran background checks
on all of you.

01:39.400 --> 01:41.101
(DOOR OPENS)

01:41.135 --> 01:43.271
Including Nurse Villanueva.

01:43.304 --> 01:46.774
Nurse Villanueva is not
a person in authority.

01:46.807 --> 01:49.377
People can be gotten to,
bribed, threatened.

01:49.410 --> 01:50.878
And don't bother
trying to hook up that IV

01:50.911 --> 01:52.613
until I know
what you want to
pump into me.

01:52.646 --> 01:55.283
They're normal IV fluids,
Mr. Stewart. Please.

01:55.316 --> 01:57.117
I'm sure you consider
whatever you give me

01:57.151 --> 01:59.119
to be normal
medical treatment,
but we all know

01:59.153 --> 02:01.622
that doctors are pushers
in the pay of the
drug companies.

02:01.655 --> 02:04.258
The bag contains
an isotonic crystalloid

02:04.292 --> 02:08.729
composed of 0.9%
sodium chloride
dissolved in sterile water.

02:08.762 --> 02:11.131
Also, given that
we will soon be

02:11.165 --> 02:12.900
drugging you
into unconsciousness

02:12.933 --> 02:14.868
and cutting into
your body,

02:14.902 --> 02:16.604
don't you have to
trust us a little?

02:18.972 --> 02:20.741
You must be
the autistic guy.

02:20.774 --> 02:22.576
Good. No bull.

02:22.610 --> 02:24.144
Probably doesn't know
what bull is.

02:24.178 --> 02:26.714
Bet your parents got
one of those
combination vaccinations.

02:26.747 --> 02:31.285
Not connected, because
science does not support
an autism link.

02:32.152 --> 02:33.287
Yeah, that's what
they told you.

02:33.321 --> 02:36.190
Mr. Stewart, suppose
we focus on what
we'll be doing

02:36.224 --> 02:39.227
to halt the liver damage
caused by your
genetic condition.

02:39.260 --> 02:40.628
Idiopathic portal hypertension
can cause...

02:40.661 --> 02:43.397
My liver is damaged,
but that's not the cause.

02:43.431 --> 02:44.598
I've been poisoned.

02:44.632 --> 02:46.967
**

02:51.305 --> 02:53.374
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

03:01.649 --> 03:04.252
His internist
heard the same theory.

03:04.285 --> 03:06.320
Tox screen
came back negative.

03:06.354 --> 03:08.822
And KCNN3 genetic testing
confirmed the cause

03:08.856 --> 03:10.991
of his idiopathic
portal hypertension.

03:11.024 --> 03:13.193
He inherited it
from his mother.

03:13.227 --> 03:14.628
Worth running
that tox screen again?

03:16.196 --> 03:17.698
The guy has a web show
where he claims

03:17.731 --> 03:20.668
the parents of children
who died in school shootings
are "crisis actors."

03:20.701 --> 03:22.169
He's earned some enemies.

03:22.202 --> 03:23.604
Once we start
doubting the tests,

03:23.637 --> 03:24.805
then you can't trust
anything

03:24.838 --> 03:26.340
and there's no point
in anything.

03:26.374 --> 03:28.376
We know our patient
needs liver shunt surgery.

03:28.409 --> 03:29.843
We're doing the surgery.

03:29.877 --> 03:30.944
DR. REZNICK: You were late.

03:30.978 --> 03:32.613
Your mom
keeping you up?

03:32.646 --> 03:35.015
Singing at night again?

03:35.048 --> 03:36.384
No.

03:36.417 --> 03:37.418
She's been quiet.

03:39.920 --> 03:42.055
Ms. Barstow,
I'm Dr. Browne.

03:42.089 --> 03:43.291
This is Dr. Reznick.

03:43.324 --> 03:44.358
What seems to be
the trouble?

03:44.392 --> 03:46.327
Nothing much, really.

03:46.360 --> 03:48.862
I feel silly for coming here,
but Jonas insisted.

03:48.896 --> 03:50.298
Because you aren't
getting any better.

03:50.331 --> 03:52.466
Lily likes to downplay
her problems.

03:52.500 --> 03:54.502
She's the rock,
and I'm the wimp.

03:54.535 --> 03:56.404
Ah, fuss, fuss, fuss.

03:56.437 --> 03:59.072
I've just been
a little off food
for a few days.

03:59.106 --> 04:00.374
You also have a fever.

04:00.408 --> 04:01.775
Most likely,
it's an infection.

04:05.879 --> 04:07.481
(ALARM BEEPING)

04:07.515 --> 04:09.182
Oh, my God! Lily!
(LILY COUGHS)

04:09.216 --> 04:11.084
Sir, please step back.
Lay back for me.

04:11.118 --> 04:12.420
We're gonna do
an ultrasound.

04:12.453 --> 04:13.887
(ALARM CONTINUES)

04:13.921 --> 04:16.123
**

04:17.725 --> 04:20.561
Her pulse is up.
Blood pressure's up, too.

04:20.594 --> 04:22.029
Uh...

04:23.397 --> 04:24.532
Her appendix is ruptured.

04:26.233 --> 04:27.568
Oh, my God.

04:27.601 --> 04:29.303
Page anesthesia stat!
We're taking her to the O.R.

04:31.271 --> 04:32.440
DR. PARK: We need
pre-op lab results.

04:32.473 --> 04:33.941
Patient name?

04:33.974 --> 04:36.209
Oh, we can't tell you.

04:38.946 --> 04:41.449
Celebrity track.
You'll find the results
under the ID number.

04:43.784 --> 04:46.286
Politics, arts,
business?

04:47.220 --> 04:48.556
Is it the President?

04:48.589 --> 04:50.057
I'll give you
a hint.

04:50.090 --> 04:51.291
He's less popular.

04:51.325 --> 04:52.593
(CHUCKLES)

04:53.994 --> 04:55.729
**

04:58.332 --> 04:59.733
Well,
that's disappointing.

05:07.641 --> 05:09.076
(DOOR OPENS)

05:10.478 --> 05:12.546
DR. MELENDEZ: Once
we get this cleaned up,
we need to figure out

05:12.580 --> 05:14.615
why her brain isn't getting
the right distress signals.

05:14.648 --> 05:16.249
How should
we go about that,
Dr. Browne?

05:17.184 --> 05:19.252
**

05:23.657 --> 05:26.760
DR. REZNICK: We do an fMRI.
Stimulate her and see how
her brain reacts.

05:26.794 --> 05:29.430
Sorry. You asked Claire,
but I have lunch plans.

05:37.538 --> 05:39.473
I have a question.

05:39.507 --> 05:41.141
Well, hopefully,
it's a quick one.

05:41.174 --> 05:43.477
I've cleared my schedule
for the rest of the day.

05:43.511 --> 05:46.146
Debbie and I
are going to City Hall

05:46.179 --> 05:47.381
to get married.

05:53.821 --> 05:55.423
Not gonna make
a big fuss out of it.

05:55.456 --> 05:58.959
You know, get dressed up,
turn it into a big event.

05:58.992 --> 06:02.696
After all,
we are not kids anymore.

06:06.400 --> 06:08.636
This is where you say
"Congratulations."

06:10.303 --> 06:11.338
Congratulations.

06:11.371 --> 06:12.372
Thank you.

06:13.674 --> 06:15.643
Do you and Debbie
hold hands?

06:15.676 --> 06:16.844
Yeah. Why?

06:16.877 --> 06:18.311
Is that what Carly
wants to do?

06:18.345 --> 06:19.480
Yes.

06:19.513 --> 06:21.649
She tried twice.

06:21.682 --> 06:23.817
Have you tried to explain
why it's difficult for you?

06:23.851 --> 06:24.952
No.

06:24.985 --> 06:27.254
Well, I...
I'd start with that.

06:28.321 --> 06:31.892
How can this
be important?

06:31.925 --> 06:33.961
It's a little thing.

06:33.994 --> 06:37.465
Carly and I are compatible
on so many big things,

06:37.498 --> 06:39.366
children,
geographic preferences,

06:39.399 --> 06:41.201
work priorities,
the use of headphones,

06:41.234 --> 06:43.070
potential color schemes
for our home...

06:43.103 --> 06:44.304
You have a checklist?

06:44.337 --> 06:45.606
Yes.

06:47.174 --> 06:49.409
Carly and I are still
learning about each other.

06:49.443 --> 06:50.678
It's not like
you and Debbie.

06:51.411 --> 06:53.013
You already
know these things,

06:53.046 --> 06:54.682
or you wouldn't be
getting married.

06:54.715 --> 06:57.417
**

06:57.451 --> 07:00.488
(MACHINE WHIRRING)

07:00.521 --> 07:01.689
(KNOB CLICKING)

07:02.389 --> 07:03.557
Four?

07:05.859 --> 07:07.027
(KNOB CLICKING)
Five?

07:08.562 --> 07:10.330
I'm feeling some pain.

07:10.363 --> 07:11.665
(CLICK)
We can stop.

07:11.699 --> 07:13.133
We're not
getting anything.

07:14.535 --> 07:16.369
She's fine.
We need feedback.

07:22.810 --> 07:24.044
(KNOB CLICKING)
Eight.

07:25.312 --> 07:26.980
(KNOB CLICKING)
Nine.

07:28.381 --> 07:30.017
Claire,
she's not feeling pain.

07:30.050 --> 07:32.119
The only activity
is in the parietal.

07:32.152 --> 07:35.689
Nothing in the limbic,
nothing in the anterior
cingulate cortex.

07:35.723 --> 07:36.790
She's feeling touch.

07:36.824 --> 07:38.592
But why did
she just say...
My guess?

07:38.626 --> 07:41.128
Because
she's never felt pain.

07:42.329 --> 07:43.964
She doesn't know
what it is.

07:43.997 --> 07:46.667
**

07:52.005 --> 07:54.608
(SNORING LIGHTLY)

07:54.642 --> 07:57.210
Sleep apnea.

07:57.244 --> 07:59.547
What?

07:59.580 --> 08:02.916
That poor guy over there,
I think he's got sleep apnea.

08:02.950 --> 08:05.285
Maybe he's just tired.

08:05.318 --> 08:09.623
It's... It's one of the most
important days of his life,
and he can't stay awake.

08:09.657 --> 08:12.125
Maybe you could...
You could tell him
that there are treatments.

08:12.760 --> 08:13.894
Me?

08:13.927 --> 08:15.963
Otherwise, he's gonna
keep his wife awake
snoring

08:15.996 --> 08:17.397
for the rest
of his life.

08:17.430 --> 08:18.832
It's gonna destroy
their marriage.

08:18.866 --> 08:19.933
(SCOFFS)

08:19.967 --> 08:21.902
You seem
very sure about that.

08:21.935 --> 08:23.236
(CHUCKLES)

08:23.270 --> 08:26.139
There's literally
no greater torture

08:26.173 --> 08:28.008
than not getting
a good night's sleep.

08:29.109 --> 08:30.844
All right, first of all,
I don't think you mean

08:30.878 --> 08:32.479
literally
no greater torture.

08:32.512 --> 08:34.114
Oh, no. It's true.

08:35.282 --> 08:37.117
Once when I was
in the Merchant Marine...

08:37.150 --> 08:38.351
Merchant Marines?

08:38.385 --> 08:40.788
It's... It's "Marine."
No "S."

08:40.821 --> 08:42.522
You were in
the Merchant Marines?
Mm-hmm.

08:42.556 --> 08:44.958
And we were stationed
off the Azores,

08:44.992 --> 08:47.628
and every night,
we were driven crazy

08:47.661 --> 08:51.198
by these loud,
just, like,
strangled sounds.

08:51.231 --> 08:54.034
Turns out it was just
a bunch of cagarro birds.

08:55.969 --> 08:58.471
(CHUCKLING) We were
literally hearing the sound

08:58.505 --> 09:00.741
of Daffy Duck drowning.

09:03.744 --> 09:04.812
(SIGHS)

09:04.845 --> 09:06.213
'Course,
that was nothing

09:06.246 --> 09:09.683
compared to
what happened
in Valparaiso.

09:09.717 --> 09:11.418
(EXHALES SHARPLY)

09:11.451 --> 09:12.452
Are you okay?

09:14.722 --> 09:16.724
Sorry.
(CLEARS THROAT)

09:16.757 --> 09:19.226
It's just, I...
I'm not feeling so good.

09:19.259 --> 09:20.694
You're not
feeling well?

09:20.728 --> 09:22.029
(SIGHS)

09:22.062 --> 09:23.096
I can't do this.

09:24.297 --> 09:25.398
What?

09:27.034 --> 09:28.401
Is that it?

09:28.435 --> 09:29.502
Are we finished?

09:29.536 --> 09:31.805
Yeah, we're gonna
get you out.

09:31.839 --> 09:33.741
Uh, just a couple
more questions.

09:35.876 --> 09:39.880
Your mother died age 66
of a heart attack.

09:39.913 --> 09:41.281
Were you there
when that happened?

09:43.016 --> 09:45.719
Yes.
I called the ambulance.

09:45.753 --> 09:47.187
She died
while we were waiting.

09:47.220 --> 09:48.255
(CLICK)

09:48.288 --> 09:49.757
Check the anterior
cingulate cortex.

09:52.259 --> 09:55.362
Physical pain
and emotional pain
are processed

09:55.395 --> 09:56.429
through the same areas.

09:56.463 --> 09:57.530
(MOUSE CLICKS)

09:57.564 --> 09:59.032
(COMPUTER BEEPS)
Nothing.

09:59.066 --> 10:01.534
But we don't know
how she feels about
her mother.

10:01.568 --> 10:03.470
It's your mother.
When she goes,
there is a vacuum.

10:05.105 --> 10:06.206
(CLICK)

10:06.239 --> 10:08.075
What about your husband?

10:08.108 --> 10:10.577
Has he had
any problems lately?

10:10.610 --> 10:12.946
He had a cancer scare
about a year ago.

10:12.980 --> 10:14.281
(CLICK)

10:14.314 --> 10:17.550
Slight activity here,
but it's pretty weak.

10:17.584 --> 10:19.119
You want to argue
that she doesn't like

10:19.152 --> 10:20.453
her mother
and her husband?

10:22.622 --> 10:23.657
(SIGHS)

10:24.157 --> 10:25.926
Wow. Sh...

10:25.959 --> 10:28.061
She's like... A superhero.

10:28.095 --> 10:29.797
Nothing can
really hurt her.

10:29.830 --> 10:31.799
**

10:33.466 --> 10:35.302
(WHIRRING)

10:40.640 --> 10:42.409
(WHIRRING STOPS)

10:44.277 --> 10:45.679
Is everything okay?

10:46.680 --> 10:48.481
Your right hand is red.

10:49.249 --> 10:50.317
Starting to swell.

10:52.152 --> 10:53.253
What does that mean?

10:53.887 --> 10:54.955
Infection.

10:58.658 --> 11:01.294
Hello.
Your surgery went well.

11:01.328 --> 11:03.430
If there are
no delayed complications,

11:03.463 --> 11:05.432
you should be discharged
in a few days.

11:05.465 --> 11:06.499
Hey!

11:08.301 --> 11:10.303
That's great,
but what about
the big picture?

11:10.337 --> 11:12.372
Once I'm out of here,
I'll go back to being
poisoned.

11:13.473 --> 11:16.910
You make many statements
that have been proven wrong.

11:16.944 --> 11:18.211
Do you really
believe them?

11:20.613 --> 11:23.951
You want to untangle
what's real and what's
for show?

11:23.984 --> 11:25.552
Now you're talking.

11:27.454 --> 11:28.688
Okay.

11:34.494 --> 11:37.697
Do you think
vaccination damage
is being covered up?

11:37.731 --> 11:39.933
Yes.

11:39.967 --> 11:45.005
Do you think
the parents of children
killed in school shootings

11:45.038 --> 11:46.573
are "crisis actors"?

11:47.707 --> 11:50.310
I can't answer
for individuals,
but I do believe

11:50.343 --> 11:53.313
there's a force in this
country that wants to
scam our people

11:53.346 --> 11:54.748
into laying down
their arms.

11:57.384 --> 12:01.188
But I no longer think
there's a pedo-slave-ring

12:01.221 --> 12:03.190
in a basement
under that pizza joint.

12:03.223 --> 12:05.926
That was a wrong call.

12:05.959 --> 12:08.328
What did you do
when you realized
you'd made an error?

12:08.929 --> 12:10.030
Nothing.

12:10.063 --> 12:12.132
No apologies,
no admissions.

12:12.165 --> 12:14.301
The second
you say you were wrong,

12:14.334 --> 12:16.904
they'll make it seem
like everything you
know is wrong.

12:16.937 --> 12:18.538
You can't give them
that ammunition.

12:19.472 --> 12:23.944
Then you're not really
offering the truth.

12:23.977 --> 12:26.646
Maybe if people saw you
admit you were wrong,

12:26.679 --> 12:27.948
maybe they'd
believe you more.

12:29.049 --> 12:31.852
No. There is
no middle ground.

12:31.885 --> 12:33.720
Compromise is a scam.

12:34.754 --> 12:37.524
When only one side
can get what it wants,

12:38.859 --> 12:40.393
make sure it's yours.

12:40.427 --> 12:42.729
**

12:47.734 --> 12:50.203
We have to surgically remove
all infected tissue.

12:50.237 --> 12:52.039
Immediately.
Stop it from spreading.

12:52.072 --> 12:54.541
We discovered
that Lily can't
feel pain,

12:54.574 --> 12:56.609
which is why
the appendicitis
went untreated,

12:56.643 --> 12:58.378
causing
a widespread infection.

12:58.411 --> 13:01.281
I can't feel pain?
That makes no sense.

13:01.314 --> 13:03.083
Whatever stimulation
your nerves receive,

13:03.116 --> 13:04.885
your brain doesn't
acknowledge it as pain.

13:04.918 --> 13:06.253
No, I feel pain.

13:06.286 --> 13:07.487
Do you?
Because I'm pinching you.

13:08.055 --> 13:09.256
I feel it.

13:09.289 --> 13:11.859
But you didn't jump or react.
You felt it as a touch.

13:11.892 --> 13:14.061
Physical or emotional pain,
it doesn't matter.

13:14.627 --> 13:16.096
**

13:16.129 --> 13:17.597
DR. MELENDEZ:
Okay, let's go. O.R. 2.

13:21.434 --> 13:23.670
Stop hiding.

13:25.906 --> 13:27.540
I'm not hiding.
I'm thinking.

13:27.574 --> 13:29.642
Well, I've done my thinking,
and what I've come up with is,

13:29.676 --> 13:34.114
I deserve
a better explanation
than "I can't do this."

13:34.147 --> 13:37.450
Because
that was humiliating.

13:43.056 --> 13:44.457
I'm sorry.

13:46.026 --> 13:47.260
You're sorry?

13:47.294 --> 13:48.561
What does that mean?

13:48.595 --> 13:50.663
Are we going back
tomorrow?

13:50.697 --> 13:52.132
Never? What?

13:52.165 --> 13:53.633
(SIGHS)

13:53.666 --> 13:56.436
You are the one
that proposed to me.

13:56.469 --> 13:58.138
You're the one
that told me

13:58.171 --> 14:00.473
how happy
our being together
makes you.

14:00.507 --> 14:03.010
It makes me happy.
It does.

14:03.043 --> 14:06.013
But (SCOFFS)
when I proposed to you,

14:06.046 --> 14:08.781
y-you even said,
"I don't know you."

14:08.815 --> 14:11.051
Is... Is that
what this is about?
Because I was...

14:12.219 --> 14:14.187
Because I was in
the Merchant Marine?

14:14.221 --> 14:16.123
I mean, yes, okay,
I... I... I...

14:16.156 --> 14:19.692
It makes me wonder
what else I don't
know about you.

14:19.726 --> 14:21.995
But more importantly,
it makes me realize

14:22.029 --> 14:23.863
you don't know
anything about me.

14:23.897 --> 14:25.665
I am really annoying.

14:25.698 --> 14:27.434
I'm easily irritable.

14:27.467 --> 14:29.602
Like when people
use the word "literally"

14:29.636 --> 14:31.071
about things
that aren't literal.

14:31.104 --> 14:32.906
I am impossible
to live with.

14:32.940 --> 14:34.074
Maybe literally.

14:35.875 --> 14:37.844
That's been made
very clear to me
in the past.

14:39.346 --> 14:41.248
(SIGHS)

14:41.281 --> 14:43.816
I don't want
to go two years
and get divorced.

14:46.219 --> 14:47.554
(VOICE BREAKING)
Divorcing you would hurt.

14:49.356 --> 14:51.524
**

14:52.525 --> 14:53.660
Thank you.

14:55.895 --> 14:57.864
But that's
a bunch of crap.

14:57.897 --> 14:59.266
You know that, right?

14:59.299 --> 15:02.169
We have
different personal styles.

15:02.202 --> 15:05.372
You like to examine things
from every angle,

15:05.405 --> 15:07.574
and I... I like
to take a leap

15:07.607 --> 15:09.276
into the dark
every now and then.

15:10.277 --> 15:12.812
(CHUCKLES LIGHTLY)

15:12.845 --> 15:13.880
You're right.

15:15.348 --> 15:17.084
I am not a leaper.

15:19.486 --> 15:21.354
I am a toe-dipper.

15:21.388 --> 15:22.889
(SIGHS)

15:22.922 --> 15:25.258
Takes me two hours
to get into the ocean
even when it's warm.

15:26.426 --> 15:28.128
**

15:30.030 --> 15:31.564
(SIGHS)

15:36.069 --> 15:38.038
I know that you're
good for me.

15:39.539 --> 15:42.042
And I know that
I'm good for you,
Aaron.

15:43.376 --> 15:44.744
Since meeting me,

15:44.777 --> 15:47.014
you've jumped ship
from a comfortable career

15:47.047 --> 15:49.416
because you decided
that you were
missing something.

15:49.449 --> 15:50.583
And...

15:52.285 --> 15:55.588
(CHUCKLING) You asked
a complete stranger

15:55.622 --> 15:56.789
to marry you.

15:58.725 --> 15:59.959
Who knows what's next?

16:01.161 --> 16:03.063
I guess you'll have to
keep thinking.

16:15.142 --> 16:17.177
(MONITORS BEEPING)

16:18.245 --> 16:20.147
DR. MELENDEZ: Dr. Browne,
widen the debridement.

16:20.180 --> 16:22.949
CLAIRE: Extending
the incisions proximally.

16:22.982 --> 16:24.717
DR. REZNICK:
Her husband thought
she was a rock.

16:24.751 --> 16:27.920
Turns out she's a rock
because nothing matters
to her.

16:27.954 --> 16:29.789
You're making
assumptions.

16:29.822 --> 16:32.325
We were monitoring
her reaction to pain.

16:32.359 --> 16:33.860
Love wasn't
part of the test.

16:34.361 --> 16:35.662
You care, you hurt.

16:35.695 --> 16:37.330
Maybe not Lily.

16:37.364 --> 16:40.833
She married this man.
She stayed with him
for years.

16:40.867 --> 16:44.437
Maybe for her, love can exist
without the pain of loss.

16:46.139 --> 16:47.307
That would be paradise.

16:51.511 --> 16:54.447
There is way more
necrotic tissue here
than I expected.

16:56.949 --> 16:58.017
She's gonna lose the hand.

16:58.051 --> 17:00.853
**

17:04.824 --> 17:06.659
Well, if anyone
can handle bad news...

17:14.767 --> 17:16.569
Are you going to
take my hand?

17:17.337 --> 17:18.738
Not right now, no.

17:21.541 --> 17:23.710
I don't like
to hold hands.

17:26.346 --> 17:30.683
Either we hold hands
or we don't.

17:30.717 --> 17:33.986
There's no compromise.

17:34.020 --> 17:36.189
Only one of us
can get what they want.

17:36.223 --> 17:37.557
I guess that's true...

17:37.590 --> 17:39.192
It should be me.

17:39.226 --> 17:42.562
Holding hands
makes me uncomfortable.

17:42.595 --> 17:45.232
Not holding hands doesn't
make you uncomfortable.

17:59.246 --> 18:02.715
That show we watched
the other night,

18:02.749 --> 18:04.151
it had a happy ending.

18:05.718 --> 18:08.388
Because they stopped
the story in a good place.

18:09.456 --> 18:10.890
But in real life,

18:11.791 --> 18:14.026
it's gonna get dark
and cold out there.

18:15.595 --> 18:18.097
All we have...

18:18.131 --> 18:19.232
Is this.

18:20.700 --> 18:24.070
This says
we're in it together,

18:24.103 --> 18:25.738
we've got
each other's back,

18:27.874 --> 18:30.443
that we'll hold each other up
for as long as we can.

18:31.077 --> 18:33.045
**

18:33.079 --> 18:37.884
I can say all those
things verbally.

18:37.917 --> 18:39.586
You could shout them,

18:39.619 --> 18:42.054
and it wouldn't say it
as loud as this.

18:45.325 --> 18:46.859
You said that not
holding hands

18:46.893 --> 18:48.395
wouldn't make me
uncomfortable,

18:48.428 --> 18:49.429
but it would.

18:52.499 --> 18:54.734
I would feel...

18:54.767 --> 18:56.536
(SIGHS)

18:56.569 --> 18:58.471
...separate.

18:58.505 --> 19:01.308
**

19:17.224 --> 19:19.592
(INHALES SHAKILY)

19:27.267 --> 19:30.270
(BREATHES SHAKILY)

19:30.303 --> 19:32.772
**

19:32.805 --> 19:34.307
It's all right.

19:38.278 --> 19:40.112
(CLEARS THROAT)

19:47.019 --> 19:48.355
CLAIRE: You've actually
been lucky,

19:48.388 --> 19:50.323
considering you have
no warning system.

19:50.357 --> 19:52.592
You need to be doing
self-checks...

19:52.625 --> 19:54.694
Knees, feet,
elbows, hands.

19:54.727 --> 19:57.096
Look for bruises,
discolorations.

19:57.129 --> 20:00.199
Anything at all
that changes could
be dangerous,

20:00.233 --> 20:01.501
life-threatening.

20:01.534 --> 20:03.503
DR. REZNICK:
But there's another option.

20:03.536 --> 20:06.038
Naloxone affects
the central nervous system.

20:06.072 --> 20:07.507
It's been shown
to block the action

20:07.540 --> 20:09.175
of pain-lowering
endorphins.

20:09.208 --> 20:11.611
It could give you
the ability to feel pain.

20:11.644 --> 20:14.180
I don't see the point.
I've been fine so far.

20:14.213 --> 20:15.548
Guess that sounds
a little silly.

20:15.582 --> 20:16.883
I know
I just lost a hand.

20:16.916 --> 20:19.819
But now I know
about checking myself,

20:19.852 --> 20:22.188
and I'll be
a lot more careful.

20:22.221 --> 20:24.391
**

20:34.834 --> 20:38.070
Why is one gesture
so important?

20:39.739 --> 20:41.541
Carly still pushing you
to hold hands?

20:41.574 --> 20:42.675
No.

20:42.709 --> 20:46.012
I tried, and she said
it was all right.

20:46.045 --> 20:47.580
Huh.

20:49.416 --> 20:53.219
You should
give me context
for that "Huh."

20:55.054 --> 20:57.557
She wants it.
She's just given up.

20:57.590 --> 21:00.360
Good.
(CHUCKLES) No.

21:00.393 --> 21:01.494
Not if
it's gonna bother her

21:01.528 --> 21:02.929
for the rest
of your relationship.

21:02.962 --> 21:04.564
Which may not be
very long.

21:08.234 --> 21:09.469
Huh.

21:09.502 --> 21:11.371
(TABLET BEEPS)

21:14.240 --> 21:15.274
Uh-oh.

21:19.312 --> 21:21.714
We need to do imaging
to make sure the problem
isn't the shunt,

21:21.748 --> 21:23.616
then check there isn't
a clot causing backup...

21:23.650 --> 21:25.785
The surgery was a success,
but I'm still being poisoned?

21:25.818 --> 21:28.187
No. The surgery
was a success,

21:28.220 --> 21:31.123
but your liver's
still deteriorating.
We don't know why.

21:34.327 --> 21:36.396
Jen, check me out of here.
Find another hospital.

21:36.429 --> 21:37.764
I can't approve that,
Mr. Stewart.

21:37.797 --> 21:39.298
You're in no condition
to leave the hospital...

21:39.332 --> 21:41.401
You just confirmed
that someone in this
hospital is poisoning me.

21:41.434 --> 21:43.069
You want me to cooperate
with the suspects?

21:43.102 --> 21:45.672
Another hospital
wouldn't solve
your problem.

21:46.839 --> 21:49.776
People can be gotten to.

21:49.809 --> 21:51.778
Bribed or threatened.

21:56.015 --> 21:57.950
Right. Someone here
wants to kill me.

21:57.984 --> 21:59.051
No one is trying...

21:59.085 --> 22:00.587
Let's constrain
some of these variables.

22:00.620 --> 22:02.321
One person touches me.

22:02.355 --> 22:03.523
Him.

22:04.491 --> 22:06.125
He doesn't know
how to lie.

22:06.158 --> 22:07.827
Oh, I can lie.

22:07.860 --> 22:10.597
Yes, but not successfully.
Good choice.

22:10.630 --> 22:13.132
**

22:16.869 --> 22:18.438
Will I be able
to play tennis?

22:19.005 --> 22:20.773
Yes, eventually.

22:20.807 --> 22:22.809
Funny,
I never could before.

22:22.842 --> 22:24.143
(CHUCKLES LIGHTLY)

22:25.344 --> 22:26.979
You always
take things well.

22:29.148 --> 22:31.283
We had to pick up
and move from Durham.

22:31.317 --> 22:32.885
Well, that was
for your job.

22:32.919 --> 22:34.320
No sense
in moping about it.

22:36.389 --> 22:37.890
The miscarriage.

22:43.329 --> 22:46.065
You never talked
about it, so...

22:46.098 --> 22:48.067
I never talked about it,
I didn't want
to hurt you.

22:51.237 --> 22:53.440
But did you
not talk about it

22:53.473 --> 22:55.174
because you just
weren't thinking
about it?

22:55.207 --> 22:57.209
What are
all these questions for?

22:58.511 --> 23:01.648
I thought we were
carrying the load together,

23:01.681 --> 23:03.583
knowing
how each other felt.

23:04.817 --> 23:07.454
This isn't about us.

23:07.487 --> 23:09.856
This is just
a medical condition.

23:14.193 --> 23:16.295
If I died,
would you care?

23:16.328 --> 23:19.031
**

23:20.199 --> 23:22.334
Would you miss me,
or, uh,

23:22.368 --> 23:24.637
would you just...

23:24.671 --> 23:25.838
Move on?

23:28.107 --> 23:30.710
Would you want me
to be miserable?

23:30.743 --> 23:32.011
I want it to matter.

23:32.044 --> 23:33.613
Of course it matters.

23:35.281 --> 23:36.883
You know I love you.

23:40.920 --> 23:42.388
Jonas.

23:43.222 --> 23:44.356
Maybe...

23:46.192 --> 23:48.728
You think it's love,
but it's like the pain...

23:48.761 --> 23:50.663
It just doesn't go
that deep.

23:50.697 --> 23:52.465
But isn't it possible
for me to love you

23:52.499 --> 23:54.601
without it being
all wrapped up
in suffering?

23:54.634 --> 23:56.936
But that's how it works.

23:56.969 --> 23:58.838
**

23:58.871 --> 24:02.408
When you lose someone,
it shouldn't be
like your hand.

24:02.441 --> 24:03.910
It should ache.

24:07.446 --> 24:08.447
That's right, isn't it?

24:09.782 --> 24:12.785
That's what
loss feels like?

24:17.657 --> 24:19.291
(SIGHS)

24:20.927 --> 24:23.162
**

24:24.497 --> 24:26.332
I need to get away
for a while.

24:27.734 --> 24:29.435
I'm sorry.

24:35.441 --> 24:36.876
Next, we're
going to test you

24:36.909 --> 24:39.779
for autoimmune hepatitis
and fatty liver.

24:39.812 --> 24:42.882
Those are diseases
whose symptoms
overlap yours.

24:42.915 --> 24:44.116
They might have
been masked

24:44.150 --> 24:46.318
by your idiopathic
portal hypertension.
(DOOR OPENS)

24:46.352 --> 24:47.520
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACH)

24:48.487 --> 24:50.089
Nurse Villanueva.
Welcome.

24:50.122 --> 24:51.591
But you know
I'm not gonna touch that.

24:51.624 --> 24:53.993
The dietician ordered
it for you, and I'm
required to bring it.

24:56.328 --> 25:00.099
What are you eating
if you're refusing
hospital food?

25:00.132 --> 25:01.300
Uh...

25:01.333 --> 25:03.069
80 grams of protein
a day.

25:03.102 --> 25:05.271
Kale and baby greens.
Hey.

25:05.304 --> 25:07.540
**

25:08.975 --> 25:10.643
"Leopard Spring."

25:11.978 --> 25:13.980
Jen, Dex,
you mind stepping out?

25:19.619 --> 25:20.687
(DOORS CLOSE)

25:20.720 --> 25:22.421
It's Chinese herbs.

25:22.454 --> 25:25.291
To make you feel younger,
more energetic, more...

25:25.324 --> 25:26.392
Virile.

25:26.425 --> 25:28.160
You don't feel virile?

25:28.194 --> 25:30.830
Of course I do,
but there's nothing wrong
with feeling more virile.

25:30.863 --> 25:32.699
I need strength
for the fight.

25:32.732 --> 25:34.667
**

25:36.102 --> 25:38.671
You're not talking.
Is there a problem?

25:41.340 --> 25:43.610
No. These herbs
are harmless.

25:43.643 --> 25:45.177
You asked
about my virility.

25:45.211 --> 25:46.478
I was curious.

25:46.512 --> 25:50.016
We're going to test you
for autoimmune hepatitis
and fatty liver.

25:53.219 --> 25:54.486
What's up?

25:54.520 --> 25:58.524
I tested a patient
for autoimmune hepatitis
and fatty liver.

25:58.557 --> 26:00.359
What's up with you?

26:00.392 --> 26:02.795
Our patient decided
to take the drugs.

26:02.829 --> 26:04.797
Because I guess
a husband walking out

26:04.831 --> 26:08.000
can make an impression
even on a woman
who feels no pain.

26:10.670 --> 26:12.538
That's a lot of paperwork
for two tests.

26:12.571 --> 26:14.173
They were negative.

26:14.206 --> 26:16.142
I thought
I might find something

26:16.175 --> 26:18.611
in his mother's old records
that could help,

26:18.645 --> 26:19.946
but no, no.

26:19.979 --> 26:21.814
Her case
was straightforward.

26:21.848 --> 26:24.016
His parents
were both alcoholics,

26:24.050 --> 26:26.819
but her liver was already
weakened by her condition.

26:26.853 --> 26:28.721
Parents both alcoholics?

26:28.755 --> 26:31.758
No wonder he thinks
people in authority
like to deny the truth.

26:31.791 --> 26:35.227
He's grown up now,
Claire.

26:35.261 --> 26:37.029
No longer
in that position.

26:38.364 --> 26:41.033
There's still plenty of lying
going on in the world.

26:41.067 --> 26:42.635
That's not a situation
you outgrow.

26:44.937 --> 26:46.172
Yes.

26:46.205 --> 26:48.040
There is a lot of lying.

26:51.377 --> 26:54.747
**

26:54.781 --> 26:56.448
Want to hear
my theories?

26:56.482 --> 26:58.417
Fight with your mother
is number one.

26:58.450 --> 27:00.619
You're debating
whether to throw her out.

27:02.088 --> 27:03.622
This theory explains what?

27:03.656 --> 27:05.591
Why the usually
compassionate
Dr. Claire Browne

27:05.624 --> 27:07.059
envies a woman
who feels no pain.

27:08.494 --> 27:10.730
You're miserable, torn.

27:10.763 --> 27:12.832
You don't know what
to do to make your
own pain go away.

27:13.666 --> 27:16.235
**

27:16.268 --> 27:17.804
Want to hear my theory?

27:17.837 --> 27:20.506
People that aren't you
are doing great,

27:20.539 --> 27:22.775
so you're looking for a toy
you can break,

27:22.809 --> 27:24.143
a pet you can torture.

27:28.748 --> 27:31.083
(PAGERS CHIME)

27:34.653 --> 27:35.822
Is she in pain?
No.

27:35.855 --> 27:36.956
What are her vitals?

27:36.989 --> 27:38.224
Vitals are fine.

27:38.257 --> 27:39.658
Then how can she
be in crisis?

27:39.692 --> 27:41.627
I don't know.
But she is.

27:41.660 --> 27:44.130
**

27:46.132 --> 27:47.299
Lily?

27:48.634 --> 27:50.002
Are you okay?

27:51.971 --> 27:53.505
Lily?

27:59.812 --> 28:02.481
I never noticed
how ugly the walls are.

28:02.514 --> 28:05.051
**

28:14.360 --> 28:16.996
I've discovered the cause
of your liver problem.

28:17.029 --> 28:19.198
Really? Fatty liver?
Autoimmune?

28:19.231 --> 28:20.299
I've never had
any symptoms of...

28:20.332 --> 28:22.468
No. You were
being poisoned.

28:23.502 --> 28:24.871
What?

28:24.904 --> 28:26.538
Who? Do you know who?
How?

28:28.107 --> 28:30.042
I thought
maybe the dose of herbs

28:30.076 --> 28:31.778
listed on the bottle
was wrong...

28:31.811 --> 28:33.212
There's a toxic dose
in there?

28:33.245 --> 28:35.547
No. There are no herbs
at all in here.

28:35.581 --> 28:37.149
It contains sildenafil.

28:38.717 --> 28:41.453
It's the active element
in Viagra.

28:41.487 --> 28:44.223
It promotes blood flow
in your penis.

28:44.256 --> 28:46.492
**

28:48.194 --> 28:49.195
I know what it does.

28:50.229 --> 28:52.064
They say
it's natural herbs.

28:52.098 --> 28:54.200
They lied.

28:54.233 --> 28:56.502
Your idiopathic
portal hypertension

28:56.535 --> 29:00.272
means your liver
is vulnerable to abuse.

29:00.306 --> 29:03.075
The amount of sildenafil
in here wouldn't kill
most people,

29:03.109 --> 29:06.578
but if someone
with pre-existing liver issues
took it every day...

29:07.546 --> 29:09.281
You were right.

29:09.315 --> 29:11.050
You've been
poisoning yourself.

29:11.083 --> 29:13.419
**

29:15.554 --> 29:18.124
It's good news.

29:19.725 --> 29:22.528
Those Communist bastards.

29:24.096 --> 29:26.732
I think they're based
in San Pedro.

29:29.235 --> 29:30.569
DR. REZNICK: Mr. Barstow.

29:31.971 --> 29:33.239
Is Lily all right?

29:33.272 --> 29:35.908
She's on medication
to reverse her
pain-free condition,

29:35.942 --> 29:37.443
but it's hit her hard.

29:37.476 --> 29:40.179
She's being wrung out
by all the negative
thoughts and feelings

29:40.212 --> 29:42.481
the rest of us
have all built
calluses against.

29:43.482 --> 29:44.884
But she made
the right choice?

29:44.917 --> 29:46.552
I mean, she needs
this to be safe.

29:46.585 --> 29:48.888
I don't think
she's doing this
to be safe.

29:48.921 --> 29:50.957
I think she's doing this
because you walked out.

29:53.159 --> 29:54.160
Why?

29:55.361 --> 29:57.096
You were happy
for years.

29:57.129 --> 29:59.431
Now you're sure you
can't be happy unless
your wife changes?

30:01.733 --> 30:04.736
I want her to feel
everything I feel.

30:05.905 --> 30:07.739
The love, the pain,
everything.

30:07.773 --> 30:08.908
Wouldn't you?

30:10.843 --> 30:13.112
The residents
in this hospital
work long hours.

30:13.145 --> 30:14.380
You know why?

30:14.413 --> 30:16.815
Because the surgeons in charge
worked long hours

30:16.849 --> 30:18.117
when they were residents.

30:18.150 --> 30:20.119
They suffered,
so we have to suffer.
It's human nature.

30:20.619 --> 30:21.653
What does that...

30:21.687 --> 30:23.990
But someone
like your wife,
so invulnerable,

30:24.023 --> 30:26.125
it's... It's like she's
gotten away
with something.

30:26.158 --> 30:27.826
It's hard
not to resent her.

30:27.860 --> 30:30.462
Sure,
we want to "cure" her,
but how much of it is...

30:30.496 --> 30:32.098
Is to give her
a warning system,

30:32.131 --> 30:34.833
and how much is because
we want to pull her down
into hell with the rest of us?

30:36.035 --> 30:39.005
**

30:53.352 --> 30:54.753
Are you married now?

30:54.786 --> 30:56.788
(SIGHS) No.

30:56.822 --> 30:58.057
I chickened out.

30:58.991 --> 31:00.759
Apparently,
I don't like change.

31:00.792 --> 31:02.494
Change makes me
very nervous.

31:03.629 --> 31:05.965
I'm not the easiest man
in the world to live with.

31:07.466 --> 31:09.468
My first wife
made that very clear.

31:09.501 --> 31:10.869
It's true.

31:10.903 --> 31:12.972
You can be
very irritating.

31:18.077 --> 31:19.545
Are you saying
I shouldn't get married?

31:21.680 --> 31:24.083
Are you asking
for my advice?

31:27.419 --> 31:28.487
Yes.

31:29.922 --> 31:33.759
You've never
really asked before.

31:34.893 --> 31:37.563
And this is
an important decision.

31:37.596 --> 31:39.731
Your happiness
depends on it.

31:41.133 --> 31:42.501
This is huge.

31:42.534 --> 31:44.903
**

31:48.340 --> 31:49.341
Well?

31:51.410 --> 31:53.145
Oh. I don't have
any advice.

31:53.179 --> 31:54.713
I don't even
understand the issue.

31:55.914 --> 31:58.184
I also don't understand
why you asked

31:58.217 --> 31:59.751
when you've already
made up your mind.

32:00.452 --> 32:01.920
What?

32:01.954 --> 32:05.191
You usually call her
your ex-wife.

32:05.224 --> 32:06.792
You just called her
your "first."

32:06.825 --> 32:08.327
It implies a second.

32:08.360 --> 32:10.696
**

32:19.805 --> 32:21.740
Why are you staring
in your trunk?

32:21.773 --> 32:24.143
Something in here
the answer to your problem?

32:27.579 --> 32:29.548
Yoga mat,

32:29.581 --> 32:31.283
gym bag,

32:31.317 --> 32:33.352
extra sneakers...
(GASPS)

32:33.385 --> 32:34.886
Here's a little
earthquake kit.

32:35.254 --> 32:36.455
So sensible.

32:36.488 --> 32:37.556
Dirty towel.

32:37.589 --> 32:38.824
Ooh! What's this?

32:38.857 --> 32:40.159
Put it back.

32:50.869 --> 32:51.937
It's my mom.

32:51.970 --> 32:54.173
**

33:22.068 --> 33:24.303
(LAUGHS)
Why are you jumping?

33:24.336 --> 33:26.538
I'm not jumping.
I'm leaping.

33:28.307 --> 33:30.176
Come on.
Come leap with me.

33:31.477 --> 33:33.312
We both can't leap
on that thing.

33:34.346 --> 33:35.414
Oh!

33:35.447 --> 33:37.283
(GASPS)
Are you okay?

33:40.619 --> 33:41.720
Never better.

33:42.354 --> 33:45.291
Will you leap with me...

33:45.324 --> 33:46.625
To City Hall?

33:48.860 --> 33:50.096
Yes, I will.

33:50.129 --> 33:52.731
Also, I may have
done something
to my ankle.

33:53.732 --> 33:56.068
Do you want me
to call someone...

33:56.102 --> 33:58.104
Je ne regret nothing,
baby.

33:58.137 --> 34:00.038
**

34:05.477 --> 34:10.416
I left the champagne
because I was
so ready for victory.

34:12.684 --> 34:13.752
(CHUCKLES LIGHTLY)

34:13.785 --> 34:15.721
Now I don't even
know what to do
with the damn ashes.

34:17.723 --> 34:20.792
Leave them on a shelf
in the closet
with the spare towels?

34:20.826 --> 34:22.694
Put them
down the disposal?

34:22.728 --> 34:23.862
What did she want done
with them?

34:23.895 --> 34:26.031
It was stupid.
I'm sure she was joking.

34:26.064 --> 34:27.766
Yeah, everyone jokes
in their will.

34:31.703 --> 34:33.105
The Marine Science Center.

34:37.209 --> 34:38.677
She loved sea lions.

34:38.710 --> 34:41.012
She'd take me to
see them all the time.
It was a thing.

34:41.046 --> 34:43.549
Any city we were in,
"I wonder if they
have sea lions."

34:43.582 --> 34:45.083
(CHUCKLES)

34:46.418 --> 34:48.320
You need to do it.
Now.

34:48.354 --> 34:49.755
No. No.

34:49.788 --> 34:51.056
It is a pointless gesture

34:51.089 --> 34:54.059
because my mother is dead
and she doesn't care.

34:54.092 --> 34:56.762
Perfect.
The center's open this evening
for an after-hours event.

34:59.565 --> 35:01.200
We'll have to dress up.

35:03.402 --> 35:04.903
(DANCE MUSIC PLAYS)

35:04.936 --> 35:08.540
The winner of tonight's
vote for Most Fabulous
Sea Creature,

35:08.574 --> 35:10.709
the vampire squid!

35:10.742 --> 35:12.778
(CHEERS AND APPLAUSE)

35:16.815 --> 35:18.217
I feel ridiculous!

35:18.250 --> 35:19.318
You look great.

35:19.351 --> 35:21.820
You could give
the vampire squid
a run for her money.

35:21.853 --> 35:23.422
Now let's find
the sea lions.

35:23.455 --> 35:25.591
(CHEERS AND APPLAUSE)

35:34.600 --> 35:36.001
You came back.

35:36.034 --> 35:37.135
Yeah.

35:38.937 --> 35:41.273
**

35:47.413 --> 35:49.215
(CRYING)

35:49.248 --> 35:51.283
(SNIFFLES)

35:51.317 --> 35:52.584
Thank God.

35:56.588 --> 35:57.789
We'll stop this.

35:58.757 --> 35:59.858
It'll be all right.

36:04.129 --> 36:06.665
Doctor, you got
to get this stuff
out of her IV.

36:06.698 --> 36:08.033
You don't need it.

36:09.801 --> 36:12.238
If you have to be careful
about getting hurt,

36:12.271 --> 36:13.805
I'll be there to help you.

36:16.007 --> 36:17.876
The "stuff" was removed
some time ago.

36:19.445 --> 36:20.912
Before Dr. Browne
went off-shift,

36:20.946 --> 36:23.582
she told me that Lily
was experiencing
some problems.

36:23.615 --> 36:26.852
So I thought it best
to discontinue the
medication for a while.

36:26.885 --> 36:28.587
She's as she was
when you left her.

36:28.620 --> 36:30.856
**

36:32.157 --> 36:33.492
You never cry.

36:39.565 --> 36:42.100
When I saw you
sitting there,

36:42.133 --> 36:44.570
I've never been so happy
in my whole life.

36:51.877 --> 36:53.845
(SNIFFLES)

37:01.387 --> 37:04.189
I thought you
didn't want to
"make a fuss."

37:05.524 --> 37:06.558
Yeah.

37:06.592 --> 37:08.193
Who knew?

37:08.226 --> 37:10.829
**

37:19.538 --> 37:22.140
(DANCE MUSIC PLAYS
IN DISTANCE)

37:22.173 --> 37:24.075
(SEA LIONS GRUNTING)

37:43.729 --> 37:45.263
(SIGHS)
This seems weird.

37:46.932 --> 37:48.133
It is weird.

37:49.901 --> 37:53.705
Most people have
some kind of ritual
all ready for them

37:53.739 --> 37:56.274
so they don't have to think
about this kind of stuff.

37:58.810 --> 38:00.078
You got a prayer?

38:01.447 --> 38:03.014
I'm not religious.

38:03.048 --> 38:04.950
Neither was my mom.

38:04.983 --> 38:06.618
Everybody has
a religion.

38:08.320 --> 38:11.423
Not everybody has a god,
but everybody has a religion.

38:11.457 --> 38:13.459
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

38:19.130 --> 38:20.165
Music.

38:22.334 --> 38:24.135
Your mother's religion
was music.

38:28.273 --> 38:29.274
Sing.

38:32.143 --> 38:35.313
By the sea lion colony
at a drag pride party?

38:35.347 --> 38:37.949
(CHUCKLES)

38:37.983 --> 38:41.252
Or you can just
dump it out
and feel weird.

38:42.921 --> 38:43.922
Your call.

39:12.384 --> 39:14.686
(VOICE BREAKING)
* Ama...

39:16.788 --> 39:17.856
Okay.

39:17.889 --> 39:19.858
(SIGHS, SNIFFLES)

39:24.229 --> 39:27.365
* Ama...

39:30.135 --> 39:33.071
* ...zing grace

39:37.075 --> 39:38.376
Oh, God.

39:38.410 --> 39:41.012
(SNIFFLES)

39:41.046 --> 39:43.882
* How sweet

39:45.917 --> 39:47.886
* The sound

39:52.424 --> 39:57.629
* That saved

39:57.663 --> 40:01.900
* A wretch

40:01.933 --> 40:08.073
* Like me

40:12.444 --> 40:14.212
(SNIFFLES)

40:14.245 --> 40:15.514
(SIGHS)

40:15.547 --> 40:17.916
* I once

40:20.519 --> 40:22.588
* Was lost

40:25.090 --> 40:28.594
* But now

40:30.529 --> 40:32.363
* Am found

40:32.397 --> 40:36.034
**

